To measure the photocatalytic activity of the two samples, time-dependent photodegradation of MB solution was conducted. When there was no ZnO/Si nanowire arrays in the solution, the MB dye was stable and no obvious degradation was observed under irradiation of the UV light, suggesting that the photoinduced self-sensitized photodegradation of MB was negligible. Figure 7 shows the absorption spectra of MB aqueous solutions as catalyzed by sample ALD and sample MS. The peak intensity of the post-degradation MB solution is lower than that of original solution, suggesting photocatalytic activity of the two specimens. However, the photocatalytic efficiency is decreased with an extended period. The relationship between the photocatalytic efficiency and the time period is calculated. For the MB solution, the absorption intensity at the peak position of ~665 nm can be characterized,Fig. 7
