It has been confirmed that the photodegradation of organic dye pollutants in the semiconductor catalysts is due to the presence of active species, including hydroxyl radical ⋅ OH, photogenerated hole h+, and superoxide anion radical ⋅O2−\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
